Key highlights of GARNET EQUITY CAPITAL HOLDINGS INC Q3 2015 13F Stocks


11/02/2015  by HedgeFundsTracker 
			in 13F Filings 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Key highlights of GARNET EQUITY CAPITAL HOLDINGS INC Q3 2015 13F Stocks and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/key-highlights-of-garnet-equity-capital-holdings-inc-q3-2015-13f-stocks/252534/.CaptchaSubmitGarnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc Quarterly Portfolio Highlights
 Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc just filed its quarterly 13F. Dated 02/11/2015, the filing reveals the hedge fund has a portfolio value of $205.34 million, representing an increase of $68.05 million  from the previous quarter when it was $137.29 million. Note: This filling reprents about 108.09% of Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s assets, which which are listed in the US. Does such a sizable change means that the professionals at Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc are getting more bullish on the stock market or just the opportunity on the long side is constrained? 






Portfolio Q32015Market Value:$205,340,000Previous Mkt Value:$137,290,000Chg Mkt Value %:49.57 % Sentiment:Turnover %:15.51 %




Stocks ActivityNew Purchases:2Additional Purchases:8Sold out:6Reduced:7Top 10 Holdings %:74.89%






Based on $189.98 million in assets under management, Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s equity exposure represents  108.09% of assets. 
 Fund New Positions
During this quarter, Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc new positions included Restaurant Brands Intl Inc for $3.05 million and Nordstrom Inc (JWN) for $2.87 million. These were the 2 biggest new positions. In total the hedge fund bought 2 new stocks. 






Top 5 New BuysRestaurant Brands Intl Inc1.49%Nordstrom Inc1.40%---




13F Sector AllocationFinance63 %Consumer Discretionary14 %Other7 %Consumer Staples7 %Industrials5 %






Increased Positions
 Based on this filing the hedge fund lifted its stakes in Spdr S&P 500 Etf Tr (Put) (SPY) by 733% to $95.82 million, Disney Walt Co (DIS) by 33% to $6.13 million, Wells Fargo & Co New (WFC) by 20% to $4.62 million, Cowen Group Inc New (COWN) by 39% to $4.15 million and Bojangles Inc by 38% to $2.79 million. Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc also acquired smaller stakes in Citi Trends Inc (CTRN) by 37.40% to $3.71 million, Deckers Outdoor Corp (DECK) by 100.00% to $4.06 million and Ignite Restaurant Group Inc (IRG) by 52.57% to $1.46 million. Building positions gradually is normal investment practice for many hedge funds. 
 Sold Positions
This fund sold its stakes in Mcdonalds Corp (Call) (MCD), Chuys Hldgs Inc (CHUY), Dow Chem Co (DOW), Metlife Inc (MET) and Boot Barn Hldgs Inc (BOOT). These stocks constituted 3.46 %, 2.93 %, 2.80 %, 2.04 % and 1.75 % of the fund’s portfolio, respectively. We can only speculate about the reasons for the dumping but we believe it has to do with either value, momentum or a better place for Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s capital.

Reduced Positions
The fund also slashed its postitons in Proshares Tr (SDS) by -58.33%, Spdr S&P 500 Etf Tr (SPY) by -33.33%, American Intl Group Inc (AIG) by -15.38%, Owens Corning New (OC) by -17.65% and Ethan Allen Interiors Inc (ETH) by -33.00%. 
 Top Holdings
Spdr S&P 500 Etf Tr (Put) (SPY), Spdr S&P 500 Etf Tr (SPY) and Wal (WMT) made up the majority of Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s total US long portfolio in this quarter. These securities were top 3 and constitute 54.02% of Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s US-listed securities. The top 10 securities make approximately 74.89% of the reported fund’s portfolio.

 It seems Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc holds concentrated portfolio. We wonder do they believe, same as many legendary traders, that diversification is losing approach? The table above provides an overview of Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc’s top 10 US-listed equity positions in this quarter. 
 Sector Analysis
Garnet Equity Capital Holdings Inc lifted the finance sector from 37 % to 63 %. The fund slashed the Industrials, Consumer Discretionary and Consumer Staples sector stakes by 5 %, 19 % and 26 %, respectively. 
So these are Q3 2015 fund’s sector weights now: finance 63 % for $129.36 million, consumer discretionary 14 % for $28.75 million, consumer staples 7 % for $14.37 million, industrials 5 % for $10.27 million and transports 3 % for $6.16 million.
Important Position Changes
Top 10 Q3 2015 New Positions: Restaurant Brands Intl Inc and Nordstrom Inc (JWN).
Top 10 Q3 2015 Sold Out Completely: Mcdonalds Corp (Call) (MCD), Chuys Hldgs Inc (CHUY), Dow Chem Co (DOW), Metlife Inc (MET), Boot Barn Hldgs Inc (BOOT) and Globalstar Inc (GSAT).
